cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.CC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a cryptographic primitive called Oblivious RAM (ORAM) which obfuscates access patterns to prevent privacy leakage. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new ORAM scheme called Flat ORAM which efficiently manages memory occupancy information. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper presents a new construction for secure processors. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the performance penalty of fully functional ORAMs and proposes a simpler write-only ORAM scheme. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages, but it does propose a new protocol for secure processors which may involve programming language considerations.
